speech.p:
asked the Minister of Pensions (1) the number of persons in the employ of his Department whose sole duty is to provide tuition in correct walking on artificial legs; and the number of persons in the employ of his Department whose sole duty is to provide tuition in the use of artificial arms and interchangeable attachments;

(2) the exact size of the rooms in which legless men learn to walk on their artificial legs; and the size of the rooms set aside for this purpose for legless women at the


Ministry's limb-fitting centres at Birmingham, Bristol, Cardiff, Liverpool and Manchester.
